Paper: hep-th/9911155

Date: 1999-11-19

Title: Duality in a fermion-like formulation for the electromagnetic field

Authors: Everton M. C. Abreu and Marcelo Hott (UNESP / Campus de Guaratingueta)

Comments: 4 pages. Revtex. Final version to be published in Phys. Rev. D

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D62 (2000) 027702

We employ the Dirac-like equation for the gauge field proposed by Majorana toobtain an action that is symmetric under duality transformation. We also usethe equivalence between duality and chiral symmetry in this fermion-likeformulation to show how the Maxwell action can be seen as a mass term.